the Rosato brothers 

1128
02:27:35.431 --> 02:27:37.433
and they tried to kill him.

1129
02:27:37.517 --> 02:27:39.769
He thought you double-crossed him.

1130
02:27:40.811 --> 02:27:44.148
Our people with the New York detectives
said he was half dead. scared stiff

1131
02:27:44.273 --> 02:27:46.943
and calling out loud that you'd turned on him.

1132
02:27:47.276 --> 02:27:51.447
They already had him on possession.
bookmaking. murder one and a lot more.

1133
02:27:53.282 --> 02:27:58.955
The FBI has him airtight.
He's on an army base. 24 hour guards.

1134
02:27:59.121 --> 02:28:04.043
No way we can get to him. You've opened
yourself to five counts of perjury.

1135
02:28:06.504 --> 02:28:09.507
What about Fredo?
What does he know?

1136
02:28:09.632 --> 02:28:13.219
He says he doesn't know anything.
and I believe him.

1137
02:28:13.386 --> 02:28:17.682
Roth. he played this one beautifully.

1138
02:28:25.022 --> 02:28:27.817
I'm going to talk to Fredo.

1139
02:29:07.064 --> 02:29:09.734
I haven't got a lot to say. Mike.

1140
02:29:11.360 --> 02:29:13.863
We have time.

1141
02:29:14.030 --> 02:29:17.116
I was kept pretty much in the dark.

1142
02:29:18.451 --> 02:29:20.578
I didn't know all that much.

1143
02:29:21.537 --> 02:29:26.375
What about now? Is there anything
you can help me out with?

1144
02:29:26.959 --> 02:29:29.211
Anything you can tell me now?

1145
02:29:31.130 --> 02:29:33.799
They got Pentangeli. that's all I can tell you.

1146
02:29:48.481 --> 02:29:52.234
I didn't know it was
gonna be a hit. Mike.

1147
02:29:52.401 --> 02:29:54.654
I swear to God I didn't know it was gonna be a hit.

1148
02:29:57.448 --> 02:30:01.786
Johnny Ola bumped into me
in Beverly Hills.

1149
02:30:03.621 --> 02:30:06.666
He said that he wanted to talk.

1150
02:30:08.250 --> 02:30:14.423
He said that you and Roth
were in on a big deal together.

1151
02:30:16.967 --> 02:30:21.305
And that there was something in it
for me if I could help him out.

1152
02:30:21.430 --> 02:30:25.309
He said that you were being tough
on the negotiations

1153
02:30:25.434 --> 02:30:29.772
but if they could get a little help
and close the deal fast.

1154
02:30:31.315 --> 02:30:33.859
it would be good for the family.

1155
02:30:35.444 --> 02:30:39.949
And you believed that story?
You believed that?

1156
02:30:40.116 --> 02:30:44.161
He said there was something in it
for me. on my own!

1157
02:30:44.286 --> 02:30:48.374
- I've always taken care of you. Fredo.
- Taken care of me?

1158
02:30:49.709 --> 02:30:52.503
You're my kid brother!
You take care of me?

1159
02:30:53.504 --> 02:30:57.633
Did you ever think about that?
Did you ever once think about that?

1160
02:30:58.676 --> 02:31:02.847
"Send Fredo off to do this.
send Fredo off to do that!"

1161
02:31:03.514 --> 02:31:08.018
"Let Fredo take care of some
Mickey Mouse nightclub somewhere."

1162
02:31:08.144 --> 02:31:11.188
"Send Fredo to pick somebody up
at the airport!"

1163
02:31:11.313 --> 02:31:14.358
I'm your older brother. Mike. and
I was stepped over!

1164
02:31:14.525 --> 02:31:18.320
- That's the way Pop wanted it.
- It ain't the way I wanted it!

1165
02:31:19.071 --> 02:31:23.993
I can handle things. I'm smart!
Not like everybody says.

1166
02:31:24.160 --> 02:31:28.038
Like dumb. I'm smart
and I want respect!

1167
02:31:35.713 --> 02:31:40.885
Is there anything you can tell me about
this investigation? Anything more?

1168
02:31:48.893 --> 02:31:54.940
The Senate lawyer. Questadt.
He belongs to Roth.

1169
02:32:04.617 --> 02:32:06.410
Fredo.

1170
02:32:08.871 --> 02:32:11.540
you're nothing to me now.

1171
02:32:13.292 --> 02:32:15.753
You're not a brother.
you're not a friend.

1172
02:32:17.546 --> 02:32:20.591
I don't want to know you.
or what you do.

1173
02:32:21.717 --> 02:32:24.720
I don't want to see you at the hotels.

1174
02:32:24.804 --> 02:32:27.389
I don't want you near my house.

1175
02:32:29.308 --> 02:32:33.979
When you see our mother. I wanna know
a day in advance. so I won't be there.

1176
02:32:35.564 --> 02:32:37.233
You understand?

1177
02:32:46.992 --> 02:32:48.953
Mikey.

1178
02:32:55.584 --> 02:32:59.421
I don't want anything to happen to him
while my mother's alive.

1179
02:33:49.305 --> 02:33:52.808
There's more people
than at a ballgame in here.

1180
02:33:52.975 --> 02:33:57.146
- Hey. there's Willi Cicci!
- Frankie Five-Angels...

1181
02:34:16.498 --> 02:34:19.084
<i>This committee will come to order!</i>

1182
02:34:21.837 --> 02:34:24.673
<i>- State your name. please.
- Frank Pentangeli.</i>

1183
02:34:24.757 --> 02:34:28.510
<i>- And where were you born?
- Partinico. it's outside of Palermo.</i>

1184
02:34:28.677 --> 02:34:30.679
<i>And where do you live now?</i>

1185
02:34:30.846 --> 02:34:34.892
<i>I live in an army barracks
with the FBI guys.</i>

1186
02:34:37.102 --> 02:34:41.565
<i>We have here finally a witness
that will further testify</i>

1187
02:34:41.690 --> 02:34:48.072
<i>to Michael Corleone's rule over a criminal empire that controls all of the gambling in this country. And perhaps in other countries.</i>

1188
02:34:48.364 --> 02:34:53.243
<i>This witness has had no buffer
between himself and Michael Corleone.</i>

1189
02:34:53.369 --> 02:34:56.538
<i>He can corroborate our charges on enough counts</i>

1190
02:34:56.622 --> 02:35:01.293
<i>for this committee to recommend a charge
of perjury against Michael Corleone.</i>

1191
02:35:01.460 --> 02:35:03.420
- Senator.
- Thank you. Chairman.

1192
02:35:04.797 --> 02:35:06.382
<i>Mr Pentangeli.</i>

1193
02:35:07.549 --> 02:35:13.222
<i>Mr Pentangeli. Were you a member
of the Corleone family?</i>

1194
02:35:13.389 --> 02:35:18.435
<i>Did you serve under Caporegime.
Peter Clemenza.</i>

1195
02:35:18.560 --> 02:35:23.065
<i>under Vito Corleone.
also known as the Godfather?</i>

1196
02:35:28.779 --> 02:35:31.407
<i>I never knew no Godfather.</i>

1197
02:35:33.951 --> 02:35:36.078
<i>I have my own family. Senator.</i>

1198
02:35:39.498 --> 02:35:42.084
<i>Mr Pentangeli. you...</i>

1199
02:35:42.251 --> 02:35:46.588
<i>you are contradicting a sworn statement you've
previously made to me and signed.</i>

1200
02:35:46.755 --> 02:35:50.467
<i>I ask you again. sir.
here and now under oath...</i>

1201
02:35:50.592 --> 02:35:54.805
<i>were you at any time a member of
a crime organization</i>

1202
02:35:54.930 --> 02:35:56.765
<i>headed by Michael Corleone?</i>

1203
02:35:56.849 --> 02:35:59.852
I don't know nothing about that!

1204
02:36:02.855 --> 02:36:06.859
I was in the olive oil business
with his father

1205
02:36:06.942 --> 02:36:09.611
but that was a long time ago. that's all.

1206
02:36:10.612 --> 02:36:13.699
<i>We have a sworn affidavit. We have it.</i>

1207
02:36:15.367 --> 02:36:20.080
<i>Your sworn affidavit. that you murdered
on the orders of Michael Corleone.</i>

1208
02:36:20.205 --> 02:36:24.710
<i>Do you deny this confession? And do you realize what
will happen as a result of your denial?
</i>

1209
02:36:24.793 --> 02:36:27.963
<i>Look. the FBI guys. they promised me a deal.</i>

1210
02:36:28.130 --> 02:36:33.802
<i>So I made up a lot of stuff about Michael Corleone. 
'cause that's what they wanted.</i>

1211
02:36:33.969 --> 02:36:37.973
<i>But it was all lies. Everything!</i>

1212
02:36:38.640 --> 02:36:40.893
<i>They kept saying.</i>

1213
02:36:41.060 --> 02:36:46.148
<i>"Michael Corleone did this"
and "Michael Corleone did that ".</i>

1214
02:36:47.483 --> 02:36:51.487
<i>So I said. "Yeah. sure. Why not?"</i>

1215
02:36:51.653 --> 02:36:57.826
<i>Mr Corleone. would you kindly identify for the committee
the gentleman sitting to your left?</i>

1216
02:36:57.910 --> 02:37:00.162
I can answer that.

1217
02:37:00.329 --> 02:37:02.664
His name is Vincenzo Pentangeli.

1218
02:37:03.665 --> 02:37:08.003
<i>- Is he related to the witness?</i>
- He is. I believe. his brother.

1219
02:37:08.337 --> 02:37:13.008
<i>- Will he come forward and be sworn. sir?
- Sir. this man does not understand English.</i>

1220
02:37:13.175 --> 02:37:16.178
He came at his own expense to aid his brother 
in this time of trouble.

1221
02:37:17.012 --> 02:37:20.724
He's not under subpoena and his reputation in
his own country is impeccable.

1222
02:37:20.849 --> 02:37:22.518
<i>Are you saying he knows nothing
about these matters?</i>

1223
02:37:22.601 --> 02:37:24.645
To my knowledge. nothing.

1224
02:37:24.728 --> 02:37:29.566
<i>I'm going to find out what the hell happened here!
All right. this committee is now adjourned.</i>

1225
02:37:29.691 --> 02:37:31.735
<i>- The witness is excused.</i>
- Senator!

1226
02:37:32.861 --> 02:37:36.532
Senator! This committee
owes an apology!

1227
02:37:37.032 --> 02:37:41.036
This committee owes an apology.
Apology. Senator!

1228
02:38:08.647 --> 02:38:12.651
- Michael. excuse me.
- Hello. darling.

1229
02:38:13.068 --> 02:38:16.530
The children are outside. We're going.

1230
02:38:17.865 --> 02:38:20.534
What do you mean you're going?
We're all gonna leave tomorrow.

1231
02:38:21.368 --> 02:38:23.829
Rocco?

1232
02:38:24.872 --> 02:38:27.457
I'll be in my room. Mike.

1233
02:38:30.210 --> 02:38:33.297
Michael. I'm not going back to Nevada.

1234
02:38:33.380 --> 02:38:36.842
I brought the children
to say goodbye to you.

1235
02:38:39.887 --> 02:38:42.472
I want you to know I'm very happy for you.

1236
02:38:42.639 --> 02:38:47.144
I suppose I always knew you were too smart
to let any of them ever beat you.

1237
02:38:48.562 --> 02:38:53.192
- Why don't you sit down?
- No. no I'm not going to stay long. I can't.

1238
02:38:53.358 --> 02:38:57.070
There are some things
I'd like to talk to you about.

1239
02:38:57.237 --> 02:39:02.284
Things that have been on my mind.
changes I want to make.

1240
02:39:02.451 --> 02:39:05.537
I think it's too late for changes. Michael.

1241
02:39:06.705 --> 02:39:11.418
- I promised myself l wasn't going to say anything--
- What do you mean. "too late"?

1242
02:39:16.757 --> 02:39:19.426
What really happened with Pentangeli. Michael?

1243
02:39:25.265 --> 02:39:30.437
- His brother came and helped him.
- I didn't even know he had a brother.

1244
02:39:30.604 --> 02:39:32.439
Where is he now?

1245
02:39:33.774 --> 02:39:36.443
He's on a plane. back to Sicily.

1246
02:39:37.110 --> 02:39:39.613
All he had to do was show his face.

1247
02:39:41.281 --> 02:39:46.119
It was between the brothers. Kay.
I had nothing to do with it.

1248
02:39:54.378 --> 02:39:57.923
Nobody is going!
Not you. not the kids. No.

1249
02:39:58.966 --> 02:40:02.970
You're my wife. they're my children.
I love you and I won't allow it.

1250
02:40:04.263 --> 02:40:08.100
Michael. you say you love me. and then
you talk about allowing me to leave!

1251
02:40:08.267 --> 02:40:11.979
There are things that have been going on for years between
men and women that will not change. and that's it.

1252
02:40:12.145 --> 02:40:16.066
You've become blind. Michael!
Look. look what's happened to us.

1253
02:40:16.233 --> 02:40:18.610
My god. look what's happened to our son. Michael!

1254
02:40:19.861 --> 02:40:21.405
- Don't tell me nothing's happened to him! 
- Anthony's fine!

1255
02:40:21.571 --> 02:40:24.783
- Anthony is not fine!
- I don't want to hear about it.

1256
02:40:24.950 --> 02:40:28.870
- Anthony's friends are--
- I don't want to hear about it!

1257
02:40:30.163 --> 02:40:32.249
Over!

1258
02:40:44.261 --> 02:40:47.848
At this moment
I feel no love for you at all.

1259
02:40:48.974 --> 02:40:53.979
I never thought that would ever happen.
but it has.

1260
02:41:08.327 --> 02:41:10.412
Kay...

1261
02:41:13.248 --> 02:41:15.417
We're leaving tomorrow.

1262
02:41:16.126 --> 02:41:19.296
Kay. why don't you take the kids
back to their room?

1263
02:41:19.379 --> 02:41:25.177
- Michael. you haven't heard me.
- Kay. what do you want from me?

1264
02:41:25.469 --> 02:41:31.850
Do you expect me to let you go? Do you expect me
to let you take my children from me?

1265
02:41:32.642 --> 02:41:38.231
Don't you know me? Don't you know that that's an impossibility?
That that could never happen?

1266
02:41:38.315 --> 02:41:42.194
That I'd use all my power to keep something like 
that from happening?

1267
02:41:43.028 --> 02:41:45.405
Don't you know that?

1268
02:41:47.074 --> 02:41:48.992
Kay...

1269
02:41:51.870 --> 02:41:56.500
Now in time. you'll feel differently.

1270
02:41:58.043 --> 02:42:01.004
You'll be glad I stopped you now.

1271
02:42:02.881 --> 02:42:04.883
I know that.

1272
02:42:06.885 --> 02:42:10.347
I know you blame me
for losing the baby.

1273
02:42:12.182 --> 02:42:13.225
Yes.

1274
02:42:14.518 --> 02:42:17.229
I know what that meant to you.

1275
02:42:19.272 --> 02:42:21.400
I'll make it up to you. Kay.

1276
02:42:22.275 --> 02:42:25.153
I swear I'll make it up to you. I'll...

1277
02:42:26.405 --> 02:42:28.365
I'm gonna change.

1278
02:42:29.783 --> 02:42:33.995
I'll change. I've learnt that I have
the strength to change.

1279
02:42:36.164 --> 02:42:39.126
Then you'll forget about
this miscarriage

1280
02:42:40.001 --> 02:42:44.881
and we'll have another child.
And we'll go on. you and I.

1281
02:42:46.216 --> 02:42:47.259
We'll go on.

1282
02:42:48.969 --> 02:42:50.387
Oh. Michael!

1283
02:42:51.513 --> 02:42:53.849
Michael. you are blind.

1284
02:42:55.684 --> 02:42:58.019
It wasn't a miscarriage.

1285
02:43:00.105 --> 02:43:01.606
It was an abortion.

1286
02:43:03.483 --> 02:43:08.697
An abortion. Michael.
Just like our marriage is an abortion.

1287
02:43:09.614 --> 02:43:13.034
Something that's unholy and evil!

1288
02:43:14.661 --> 02:43:16.997
I didn't want your son. Michael!

1289
02:43:17.831 --> 02:43:21.710
I wouldn't bring another one
of your sons into this world!

1290
02:43:23.628 --> 02:43:26.047
It was an abortion. Michael.

1291
02:43:26.173 --> 02:43:31.845
It was a son. a son and I had it killed
because this must all end!

1292
02:43:33.388 --> 02:43:37.517
I know now that it's over. I knew it then.

1293
02:43:38.894 --> 02:43:44.232
There would be no way. Michael.
no way you could ever forgive me.

1294
02:43:44.357 --> 02:43:49.070
Not with this Sicilian thing
that's been going on for 2.000...

1295
02:43:56.912 --> 02:43:59.831
- You won't take my children.
- I will.

1296
02:43:59.915 --> 02:44:01.833
You won't
take my children!

1297
02:44:01.917 --> 02:44:04.252
They're my children too.

1298
02:45:34.092 --> 02:45:37.679
Fredo. give this to Grandmother.

1299
02:47:52.439 --> 02:47:54.482
Don Ciccio. it's Tommasino.

1300
02:47:58.319 --> 02:48:01.406
Allow me the honour of
introducing someone.

1301
02:48:01.740 --> 02:48:04.576
My partner in America. in New York.

1302
02:48:05.243 --> 02:48:07.078
His name is Vito Corleone.

1303
02:48:07.787 --> 02:48:10.331
We'll send him olive oil from here.

1304
02:48:11.166 --> 02:48:12.584
To his company in America.

1305
02:48:17.338 --> 02:48:20.675
They're olive oil importers. Don Ciccio.

1306
02:48:30.351 --> 02:48:36.024
We'd like your blessing. and your
permission to start work.

1307
02:48:37.108 --> 02:48:40.028
Where is this young man
from New York?

1308
02:48:43.364 --> 02:48:46.493
Have him come closer.

1309
02:48:47.494 --> 02:48:50.371
I can't see him so good.

1310
02:48:57.378 --> 02:49:01.049
My respects. Don Ciccio.
Give me your blessing.

1311
02:49:03.510 --> 02:49:05.220
Bless you!

1312
02:49:07.055 --> 02:49:08.681
What's your name?

1313
02:49:14.062 --> 02:49:17.232
You took the name of this town!

1314
02:49:17.816 --> 02:49:19.567
And what's your father's name?

1315
02:49:19.692 --> 02:49:23.363
His name was... Antonio Andolini.

1316
02:49:23.738 --> 02:49:27.408
Louder. I don't hear so good.

1317
02:49:30.829 --> 02:49:34.082
My father's name was
Antonio Andolini...

1318
02:49:34.374 --> 02:49:37.085
...and this is for you!

1319
02:50:59.000 --> 02:51:01.628
Michael. say goodbye.

1320
02:52:04.857 --> 02:52:06.234
Hi. Al.

1321
02:52:18.371 --> 02:52:21.374
Tom. Can I speak with you
for a second. Tom?

1322
02:52:29.257 --> 02:52:30.967
Tom. where's Mike?

1323
02:52:32.218 --> 02:52:34.262
Waiting for you to leave.

1324
02:52:36.889 --> 02:52:41.394
- Can I talk with him?
- Sorry. Fredo. No chance.

1325
02:52:41.978 --> 02:52:45.273
- Can I see him?
- He's in the boathouse.

1326
02:52:58.411 --> 02:53:00.788
Michael. it's Connie.

1327
02:53:22.018 --> 02:53:23.603
Michael...

1328
02:53:26.647 --> 02:53:30.109
I'd like to stay close to home now.
if it's all right.

1329
02:53:38.659 --> 02:53:40.870
Is Kay coming?

1330
02:53:43.331 --> 02:53:44.999
No.

1331
02:53:53.132 --> 02:53:55.968
Michael. Fredo's in the house with Mama.

1332
02:53:56.052 --> 02:54:00.014
He asked for you
and Tom said you wouldn't see him.

1333
02:54:03.643 --> 02:54:05.520
That's right.

1334
02:54:08.356 --> 02:54:11.692
Kids. why don't you go outside
for a while?

1335
02:54:15.238 --> 02:54:17.657
Michael. please. I want to talk to you.

1336
02:54:29.210 --> 02:54:33.214
Michael. I hated you for so many years.

1337
02:54:33.673 --> 02:54:39.011
I think that I did things to myself.
to hurt myself. so that you'd know

1338
02:54:42.223 --> 02:54:44.350
that I could hurt you.

1339
02:54:50.439 --> 02:54:54.777
You were just being strong for all of us.
the way Papa was.

1340
02:54:55.403 --> 02:54:57.280
And I forgive you.

1341
02:55:01.951 --> 02:55:03.911
Can't you forgive Fredo?

1342
02:55:04.954 --> 02:55:09.584
He's so sweet.
and helpless without you.

1343
02:55:15.923 --> 02:55:19.760
You need me. Michael.
I want to take care of you now.

1344
02:55:29.604 --> 02:55:31.147
Connie.

1345
02:57:13.374 --> 02:57:15.960
Tom. sit down.

1346
02:57:27.722 --> 02:57:31.434
Our friend and business partner.
Hyman Roth. is in the news.

1347
02:57:32.810 --> 02:57:36.230
- Did you hear about it?
- I hear that he's in Israel.

1348
02:57:36.397 --> 02:57:37.398
Mmm-hmm.

1349
02:57:38.065 --> 02:57:42.611
The High Court in Israel turned down his request
to live there as a returned Jew.

1350
02:57:42.778 --> 02:57:46.407
His passport's been invalidated. except for
return to the United States.

1351
02:57:46.490 --> 02:57:49.243
He landed in Buenos Aires yesterday.

1352
02:57:49.577 --> 02:57:53.414
He offered the gift of a million dollars
if they'd let him live there.

1353
02:57:54.415 --> 02:57:58.419
- They turned him down.
- He's going to try Panama.

1354
02:57:58.502 --> 02:58:03.174
Panama won't take him.
Not for a million. not for ten million.

1355
02:58:03.591 --> 02:58:08.262
His medical condition is reported as terminal. 
He's only gonna live another six months anyway.

1356
02:58:08.429 --> 02:58:11.432
He's been dying of the same heart attack
for 20 years.

1357
02:58:11.599 --> 02:58:13.309
That plane goes to Miami.

1358
02:58:13.434 --> 02:58:15.770
All right.
That's where I want it met.

1359
02:58:16.937 --> 02:58:22.276
Mike. that's impossible. They'll turn him over directly to the
Internal Revenue. Customs and half the FBI.

1360
02:58:22.443 --> 02:58:25.696
It's not impossible.
Nothing is impossible.

1361
02:58:25.780 --> 02:58:27.239
It would be like trying to kill the President.

1362
02:58:27.323 --> 02:58:31.786
- There's no way we can get to him!
- Tom. you know. you surprise me.

1363
02:58:34.622 --> 02:58:38.250
If anything in this life is certain.

1364
02:58:38.334 --> 02:58:41.545
if history has taught us anything.

1365
02:58:41.629 --> 02:58:44.215
it's that you can kill anyone.

1366
02:58:49.553 --> 02:58:54.475
- Rocco?
- Difficult. Not impossible.

1367
02:58:54.809 --> 02:58:56.519
Good.

1368
02:58:58.979 --> 02:59:02.650
Why did you ask me if something
was wrong when I came in?

1369
02:59:06.320 --> 02:59:09.657
I thought you were
going to tell me that

1370
02:59:09.740 --> 02:59:12.159
you were moving your family to Vegas

1371
02:59:13.536 --> 02:59:17.415
and that you'd been offered the Vice
Presidency of the Houstan hotels there.

1372
02:59:19.542 --> 02:59:24.380
- I thought you'd tell me that.
- I turned them down. I mean. do I have to tell you about every offer that I turn down?

1373
02:59:28.592 --> 02:59:31.387
- Let's do business.
- All right.

1374
02:59:33.264 --> 02:59:36.350
Just consider this. Michael.
Just consider it.

1375
02:59:37.518 --> 02:59:39.687
Now Roth and the Rosatos are on the run.

1376
02:59:39.770 --> 02:59:42.356
Are they worth it.
are they strong enough?

1377
02:59:42.773 --> 02:59:47.695
Is it worth it? You've won.
Do you wanna wipe everybody out?

1378
02:59:47.778 --> 02:59:53.075
I don't feel I have to wipe everybody
out. Tom. Just my enemies. that's all.

1379
03:00:00.791 --> 03:00:03.544
You gonna come along with me in these things
I have to do. or what?

1380
03:00:05.588 --> 03:00:11.051
Because if not. you can take your wife.
your family and your mistress

1381
03:00:11.218 --> 03:00:14.388
and move them all to Las Vegas.

1382
03:00:17.433 --> 03:00:22.480
Why do you hurt me. Michael? I've always
been loyal to you. I mean. what is this?

1383
03:00:27.067 --> 03:00:28.736
So... you're staying?

1384
03:00:30.779 --> 03:00:33.115
Yes. I'm staying.

1385
03:00:35.701 --> 03:00:37.828
What is it that you want me to do?

1386
03:00:38.329 --> 03:00:40.372
Hey. Anthony.

1387
03:00:40.873 --> 03:00:45.544
Anthony. how would you like it if I taught you
how to catch the really big fish?

1388
03:00:45.628 --> 03:00:48.088
- Would you like that?
- Okay.

1389
03:00:48.255 --> 03:00:50.883
You know. when I was your age.

1390
03:00:51.383 --> 03:00:58.265
I went out to fishing with all my brothers
and my father. Everybody.

1391
03:00:59.433 --> 03:01:02.937
I was the only one that caught a fish.

1392
03:01:03.771 --> 03:01:07.983
Nobody else could catch one except me.
Do you know how I did it?

1393
03:01:09.610 --> 03:01:13.364
Every time I put the line in the water
I said a Hail Mary

1394
03:01:13.531 --> 03:01:17.159
and every time I said a Hail Mary.
I caught a fish.

1395
03:01:19.620 --> 03:01:23.791
Do you believe that? It's true.
That's the secret.

1396
03:01:25.834 --> 03:01:29.672
- Do you want to try it when we go out on the lake?
- Okay.

1397
03:01:31.465 --> 03:01:32.633
What else you got?

1398
03:01:59.326 --> 03:02:01.787
Everything will be okay. Frankie. don't worry.

1399
03:02:02.079 --> 03:02:06.000
- Did my brother go back?
- Yeah. don't worry.

1400
03:02:06.166 --> 03:02:11.088
He's ten times tougher than me.
my brother. He's old-fashioned.

1401
03:02:12.131 --> 03:02:15.467
He didn't want to go out to dinner.
he just wanted to go straight home.

1402
03:02:15.551 --> 03:02:20.556
That's my brother! Hey listen. nothing could get
him away from that two-mule town.

1403
03:02:20.723 --> 03:02:24.560
He could have been big here.
He could have had his own family.

1404
03:02:29.815 --> 03:02:31.734
Tom.

1405
03:02:32.443 --> 03:02:35.029
what do I do now?

1406
03:02:35.738 --> 03:02:37.740
Frankie.

1407
03:02:42.286 --> 03:02:46.332
You were always interested
in politics and history.

1408
03:02:47.791 --> 03:02:51.253
I remember you talking about Hitler
back in '33.

1409
03:02:51.420 --> 03:02:55.049
Yeah. I still read a lot.
I get good stuff in there.

1410
03:02:57.593 --> 03:03:03.349
You were around the old-timers. who dreamed of how the 
family's should be organized.

1411
03:03:03.474 --> 03:03:08.896
based on the old Roman legions
and called them regimes--the Capos and the soldiers.

1412
03:03:10.147 --> 03:03:14.193
- And it worked.
- Yeah. it worked.

1413
03:03:14.943 --> 03:03:18.447
Those were the great old days.
you know.

1414
03:03:18.614 --> 03:03:21.784
We was like the Roman Empire.

1415
03:03:21.867 --> 03:03:25.329
The Corleone family
was like the Roman Empire.

1416
03:03:27.706 --> 03:03:29.667
Yeah.

1417
03:03:29.833 --> 03:03:32.211
it was once.

1418
03:03:36.632 --> 03:03:38.175
Frankie.

1419
03:03:48.644 --> 03:03:52.189
When a plot
against the Emperor failed

1420
03:03:53.440 --> 03:03:56.902
the plotters were always
given a chance

1421
03:03:58.862 --> 03:04:02.449
to let their families keep their fortunes.
Right?

1422
03:04:02.533 --> 03:04:04.702
Yeah. but only the rich guys. Tom

1423
03:04:04.785 --> 03:04:09.748
The little guys got knocked off and all
their estates went to the Emperors.

1424
03:04:09.915 --> 03:04:15.129
Unless they went home and killed
themselves. then nothing happened.

1425
03:04:16.296 --> 03:04:20.592
And their families. their families were taken care of. Tom.

1426
03:04:22.219 --> 03:04:25.597
That was a good break. a nice deal.

1427
03:04:26.265 --> 03:04:27.766
Yeah.

1428
03:04:28.642 --> 03:04:30.769
They went home

1429
03:04:31.937 --> 03:04:34.940
and sat in a hot bath

1430
03:04:35.107 --> 03:04:37.609
opened up their veins

1431
03:04:37.776 --> 03:04:40.487
and bled to death.

1432
03:04:41.655 --> 03:04:45.826
And sometimes they had a little party
before they did it.

1433
03:04:50.998 --> 03:04:54.793
Don't worry about anything.
Frankie Five-Angels.

1434
03:04:54.960 --> 03:04:58.297
Thanks. Tom. Thanks.

1435
03:05:16.732 --> 03:05:19.860
- See you. Tom.
<i>- Addio.</i> Frankie.

1436
03:05:30.829 --> 03:05:33.916
Kay. You have to go.

1437
03:05:35.709 --> 03:05:39.046
- So pretty...
- Kay. please hurry. He's coming.

1438
03:05:47.888 --> 03:05:51.725
Anthony. Kiss Mama goodbye.

1439
03:05:54.269 --> 03:05:57.064
Anthony. will you kiss your mother goodbye!

1440
03:05:57.231 --> 03:06:02.319
Anthony. say goodbye to Mama.
Anthony. I love you. Anthony.

1441
03:06:03.445 --> 03:06:05.906
Kay. please.

1442
03:06:08.742 --> 03:06:10.744
All right.

1443
03:06:23.966 --> 03:06:26.343
Mary. come here.

1444
03:06:33.600 --> 03:06:35.102
Anthony.

1445
03:06:35.185 --> 03:06:38.188
Anthony. please. Kiss me once.

1446
03:08:17.371 --> 03:08:19.456
Easy.

1447
03:08:25.128 --> 03:08:28.215
Anthony! Anthony!

1448
03:08:28.382 --> 03:08:31.385
- He's here. we're going fishing.
- No!

1449
03:08:31.551 --> 03:08:34.888
Michael wants to take him to Reno now.

1450
03:08:34.972 --> 03:08:36.974
Shit!

1451
03:08:38.225 --> 03:08:41.645
Okay. kid. you have to go to Reno
with your pop.

1452
03:08:42.604 --> 03:08:46.566
- I'll take you fishing tomorrow. okay?
- Okay.

1453
03:08:50.237 --> 03:08:51.780
Hey. Anthony.

1454
03:08:51.905 --> 03:08:56.243
Listen. I'll catch one for you in secret.

1455
03:09:00.247 --> 03:09:01.623
Okay. Al. let's go.

1456
03:09:40.787 --> 03:09:44.958
- Mr Roth. you understand I have to take you into custody.
- Yes. I understand.

1457
03:09:45.125 --> 03:09:48.295
What's your reaction
to the Israeli High Court ruling?

1458
03:09:48.462 --> 03:09:51.214
I'm a retired investor on a pension.

1459
03:09:51.381 --> 03:09:56.303
I went to Israel because I wished to live there as a Jew.
in the twilight of my life.

1460
03:10:02.642 --> 03:10:06.229
Hey. Frankie! Come on out.
let's play some Hearts.

1461
03:10:14.404 --> 03:10:16.156
Frankie!

1462
03:10:32.005 --> 03:10:34.883
Is it true you're worth
over 300 million dollars?

1463
03:10:35.050 --> 03:10:38.678
I'm a retired investor.
living on a pension.

1464
03:10:38.845 --> 03:10:42.390
I came home to vote
in the presidential election

1465
03:10:42.557 --> 03:10:44.851
because they wouldn't give me
an absentee ballot.

1466
03:10:58.365 --> 03:11:00.742
Jesus Christ.

1467
03:11:01.785 --> 03:11:06.414
Hail Mary. full of grace.
The Lord is with thee.

1468
03:11:07.916 --> 03:11:10.544
Blessed art thou amongst women.

1469
03:11:11.294 --> 03:11:14.422
Blessed is the fruit of thy womb. Jesus.

1470
03:11:15.632 --> 03:11:19.886
Holy Mary. Mother of God.
pray for us sinners.

1471
03:12:01.761 --> 03:12:06.933
Hey! Everybody. pay attention.
This is my friend Carlo Rizzi.

1472
03:12:07.767 --> 03:12:10.437
- You know my brother Fredo.
- Sure.

1473
03:12:10.604 --> 03:12:15.400
This is my stepbrother Tom.
and that's his girl Theresa.

1474
03:12:15.483 --> 03:12:18.778
This cute little thing over here. this is my sister Connie. I was telling you about her.

1475
03:12:18.862 --> 03:12:21.740
Come on. say hello to Carlo.
He's good-looking. isn't he?

1476
03:12:21.823 --> 03:12:23.366
Yes.

1477
03:12:23.533 --> 03:12:27.621
Oh. that droopy thing over there. that's my brother. Mike.
We call him Joe College. you know what I mean?

1478
03:12:28.121 --> 03:12:31.958
Go on. sit down. Talk to each other.

1479
03:12:32.125 --> 03:12:34.336
Hey. Mr Einstein...

1480
03:12:37.672 --> 03:12:40.175
- Here's the cake.
- Hey. Sally. get in here!

1481
03:12:40.342 --> 03:12:42.469
- I was scared.
- Come on.

1482
03:12:43.136 --> 03:12:46.473
- Where's your father?
- Took him on a wild goose chase. Christmas shopping.

1483
03:12:46.640 --> 03:12:49.017
Let's see that thing.

1484
03:12:50.727 --> 03:12:52.646
- Oh. honey. that's nice.
- That's beautiful.

1485
03:12:52.729 --> 03:12:56.650
- Should I put the candles on now?
- Go on. You help her. Carlo. all right?

1486
03:12:57.692 --> 03:13:00.820
- What is that? Rum?
- Yeah.

1487
03:13:05.825 --> 03:13:09.162
Sonny. come on. don't touch
the antipasto till Pop sees it.

1488
03:13:09.329 --> 03:13:11.998
He's not ugly...

1489
03:13:17.504 --> 03:13:23.677
What do you think. the nerve of them Japs. them slanty-eyed bastards? Dropping bombs on our own backyard. On Pop's birthday. you know?

1490
03:13:23.760 --> 03:13:27.222
They didn't know it was Pop's birthday.

1491
03:13:27.347 --> 03:13:30.016
Well. we should've expected it
after the oil embargo.

1492
03:13:30.183 --> 03:13:34.688
What do you mean. expected it? Expected or not. they got no right dropping bombs.
What are you a Jap-lover or something? You on their side?

1493
03:13:34.854 --> 03:13:38.441
- I understand 30.000 men enlisted this morning.
- Bunch of saps...

1494
03:13:38.608 --> 03:13:42.112
- Why are they saps?
- Sonny. come on. do we even have to talk about the war?

1495
03:13:43.238 --> 03:13:45.073
You talk to Carlo. all right?

1496
03:13:47.033 --> 03:13:50.620
They're saps because they risk their lives for strangers.

1497
03:13:50.745 --> 03:13:54.165
- That's Pop talking.
- You're goddamn right that's Pop talking.

1498
03:13:54.291 --> 03:13:58.128
- They risk their lives for their country.
- Your country ain't your blood. You remember that.

1499
03:13:58.211 --> 03:14:04.134
- I don't feel that way.
- "I don't feel that way." Well. if you don't feel like that. then why don't you just quit college and go to join the army!

1500
03:14:04.217 --> 03:14:05.719
I did.

1501
03:14:06.636 --> 03:14:09.597
I enlisted in the Marines.

1502
03:14:11.891 --> 03:14:15.103
- Mike. why didn't you come to us?
- What do you mean?

1503
03:14:15.228 --> 03:14:19.399
- Pop had to pull a lot of strings to get you a deferment.
- I didn't ask for it.

1504
03:14:20.150 --> 03:14:22.235
I didn't ask for a deferment. I didn't want it.

1505
03:14:23.403 --> 03:14:25.905
Come on! Come on. knock it off. come on!

1506
03:14:26.072 --> 03:14:29.743
- Punk!
- Sonny. Sonny. sit down.

1507
03:14:32.746 --> 03:14:35.707
Mommy. Daddy's fighting again!

1508
03:14:39.336 --> 03:14:42.088
Go show Carlo the tree.

1509
03:14:52.432 --> 03:14:54.017
Nice.

1510
03:14:55.852 --> 03:14:57.437
Nice.

1511
03:14:57.979 --> 03:15:00.690
Break your father's heart
on his birthday.

1512
03:15:01.775 --> 03:15:04.569
That's swell. Mike. Congratulations.

1513
03:15:04.652 --> 03:15:06.780
That's right. encourage him.

1514
03:15:06.863 --> 03:15:09.616
Go on. get me a drink. Go on!

1515
03:15:13.453 --> 03:15:16.956
You gotta understand.
Your father has plans for you.

1516
03:15:17.123 --> 03:15:21.294
Many times he and I have talked
about your future.

1517
03:15:23.129 --> 03:15:26.966
You talked to my father about my future?

1518
03:15:28.176 --> 03:15:32.514
- My future.
- Mikey. he has high hopes for you.

1519
03:15:32.639 --> 03:15:38.144
- Well. I have my own plans for my future.
- Did you go to college to get stupid? You're really stupid.

1520
03:15:38.228 --> 03:15:40.146
He's here! Come on!

1521
03:15:42.065 --> 03:15:44.025
Come on.

1522
03:15:46.319 --> 03:15:48.238
Stupid!

1523
03:16:05.588 --> 03:16:07.924
Surprise!

1524
03:16:10.969 --> 03:16:13.221
<i>For he's a jolly good fellow</i>

1525
03:16:13.304 --> 03:16:16.641
<i>For he's a jolly good fellow</i>

1526
03:16:16.724 --> 03:16:20.520
<i>That nobody can deny
Nobody can deny...</i>
